com.paydiant.android.common.util

Class PaydiantLoggingUtility

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.common.util.PaydiantLoggingUtility
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISDKLoggingUtility

    public class PaydiantLoggingUtility
extends Object
implements ISDKLoggingUtility
    Singleton class to provide support for submitting log messages. This class uses the PaydiantLoggingService android service to send the log messages, so the service needs to be included in the AndroidManifest.xml.
    Author:
    Paydiant

        sendDataInBackground - Whether to support sending log entries when the app is in background.

      • addSuccessLogMessage

        public void addSuccessLogMessage(String eventType,
                        LinkedHashMap<String,String> eventParameters)
        Adds a log message for a successful event that is external to the events provided for the operations in this SDK. These events may include operations which are specific to an app implementation like social media events, branch/store location search events etc..

        Note: Do not use this method to log events for any operations offered by the SDK. Use addSuccessLogMessage(PaydiantLoggingEventType, LinkedHashMap) instead.
        Parameters:
        eventType - event type of the successful external event.
        eventParameters - Additional parameters that needed to be passed along with the successful event, if applicable.
        Since:
        4.0.0.2

      • setLastFailedEventDisplayMessage

        public void setLastFailedEventDisplayMessage(String displayMessage)
        Sets the displaying error message for the most recent failed logging event. When the SDK's internal logging is enabled, this method must be called to complete logging the failed log message entry, as the displaying error message is not known to the SDK during the time the failure event is internally logged.
        Note: Calling this method right before displaying the error message would be ideal, since some of the logging events such as payment failures, registration failures require sending the log messages to the server, soon after the failed event occurs.

        Core services sample: 
        
 IPaymentAccountManagerFacade paymentAccountManagerFacade = ...;
 try {
     TenderTypeList tenderTypeList = paymentAccountManagerFacade.retrieveAllTenderTypes();
     ...
 } catch (PaydiantException e) {
     String errorMessage = getString(R.string.tender_type_retrieve_error);
     PaydiantLoggingUtility.getInstance().setFailedLogDisplayMessage(errorMessage);
     showAlert(errorMessage);
 }

        UI services sample: 
        
 IPaymentAccountManagementService paymentAccountManagementService = ...;
 paymentAccountManagementService.setPaymentAccountRetrieveListener(new PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter() {
 
   @Override
   public void onRetrieveAllTenderTypesSuccess(TenderTypeList tenderTypeList) {
       ...
   }
   
   @Override
   public void onPaymentAccountManagerError(PaydiantException e) {
       String errorMessage = getString(R.string.tender_type_retrieve_error); 
       PaydiantLoggingUtility.getInstance().setFailedLogDisplayMessage(errorMessage);
       showAlert(errorMessage);
   }
 
 });
 paymentAccountManagementService.retrieveAllTenderTypes();
        Parameters:
        displayMessage - - Error message displaying for the most recent failure event
        Since:
        4.7.0.2

      • setCustomAppVersionName

        public void setCustomAppVersionName(String appVersionName)
        Provides the ability to specify a custom appVersionName value for logging. By default the appVersionName is retrieved from the AndroidManifest.xml, however setting this will overwrite the retrieved values.
        Parameters:
        appVersionName - - A custom appVersionName value that will be sent to logs.
        Since:
        5.9.0.1.a
